article.description: — Justin Hill had 20 points as Longwood rolled past Hampton 73-49 on Monday night.
article.headline: Hill scores 20 to lift Longwood over Hampton 73-49
article.linkText: Hill scores 20 to lift Longwood over Hampton 73-49
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. -- — Justin Hill had 20 points as Longwood rolled past Hampton 73-49 on Monday night. Isaiah Wilkins had 11 points and six rebounds for Longwood (13-5, 5-0 Big South Conference), which won its sixth consecutive game. Jaylani Darden added three blocks. Hampton scored 17 first-half points, a season low for the team. Najee Garvin had 15 points for the Pirates (5-11, 1-4). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
